{
  "texts": [
    "Technology has the inherent potential to provide students with a higher calibre of education, equipping them with the requisite problem-solving proficiencies demanded within diverse domains (Meyen et al., 2006).",
    "Specific technological tools enable students to interact with information through visual and tactile modalities, thereby fostering deeper comprehension and augmenting their capacity to acquire knowledge.",
    "It is widely acknowledged that technology can enrich the educational experience, rendering the process of learning and teaching more pertinent, captivating and meaningful for students, and ultimately culminating in enhanced subject mastery (Karasavvidis & Kollias, 2014).",
    "In recent times, various educational software tools have been employed as instructional aids in mathematics education (e.g.",
    "Autograph, Cabri II, Cabri 3D, Coypu, Cinderella, Derive, Geometer's Sketchpad, and Graphmatica, among others)."
  ]
}